      "writtenOn": "2026-04-14T11:57:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "always lowercasing keys and sections seems worrying; https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/INI_file#Case_sensitivity says that Windows treats these as case insensitive and Unix-style generally doesn\u0027t. Note that this doesn\u0027t mean lowercasing on Windows, it just means the interpretation is case insensitive.\n\nSo I think this needs to be an option from day one, like `CaseSensitivity CaseSensitivityStrategy`, where the type is an enum with the options like LowerCase and CaseSensitive.",
      "revId": "c19192da9b9b57484f5330af839aab30fa6192a6",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
