      "writtenOn": "2026-04-14T11:57:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this func is only used once; inline it\n\nwhen you inline it, note that the caller already handles quoted strings. so when the value begins with a quote, you can reuse the work of finding the closing quote.\n\nalso, what happens when a line is like `key \u003d \"value` or `key \u003d value\"`, should those fail or work?",
      "revId": "c19192da9b9b57484f5330af839aab30fa6192a6",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a02a1376_d7595f60",
        "filename": "encoding/ini/decode.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 189,
      "author": {
        "id": 1039294
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-17T07:20:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "After giving it a second thought, since INI treats all values as strings by default, it probably would make more sense to treat any quotes in the values as literals, especially when escape sequences are parsed as literals too. Otherwise, there\u0027s no way for user to specify quotes in the cases where the quotes do have their meanings.\n\nI\u0027ve made the changes in the code accordingly. Please let me know what you think.",
      "parentUuid": "668b261e_3e27efb6",
      "revId": "c19192da9b9b57484f5330af839aab30fa6192a6",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "90eb887b_15c84ac7",
        "filename": "encoding/ini/decode.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 280,
      "author": {
        "id": 1017720
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-14T11:57:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "note that this passively accepts any valid Go int or float representation; that\u0027s probably too lax for INI. what formats should we accept here?\n\ne.g. I think only accepting valid JSON ints or strings could be a better starting point than accepting Go. At least JSON is a more widespread standard.\n\nBut I have no clue in terms of what INI actually accepts. Ideally we stick with INI\u0027s common denominator, and anything else can be a config option.",
      "revId": "c19192da9b9b57484f5330af839aab30fa6192a6",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
